    <div class="faq-a" id="are-ai-content-detectors-accurate"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Accuracy varies widely. Vendors claim 95-99% accuracy, but independent tests show 65-90% on clean AI text and below 50% on paraphrased or edited content. The Stanford study found a 61% false positive rate on essays by non-native English speakers. Use detector results as one signal, not as proof.</p></div></div>
