    <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For SEO purposes, running AI detection on your own content serves one purpose: quality control. If a detector flags your content as highly likely AI-generated, that may signal the content is too predictable, too uniform, or lacking original insight. Those are legitimate quality concerns worth addressing.</p>
<p>Do not run detection as a pass/fail gate. Use it as a quality signal. If the content is helpful, accurate, and well-written, the detection score is irrelevant for Google rankings.</p>
